cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.ST

The paper deals with statistical learning and algorithmic techniques for controlling variance and achieving high probability bounds. This is a common theme in machine learning and statistics, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of confidence bounds, and data structures (cs.DS) in the form of online-to-batch conversion. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization techniques for exp-concave functions, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistics (cs.ST).
